	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>what you posted is a very viable tactic for soloers. However, I have to point out that in a few more levels unless you start choosing your mobs very carefully, you are going to die right alongside your fire pet. I understand the value of "distracting" the mob in order for your pet to get off more damage. I used to do that also, until I met crag spiders, whom I got about 4 levels off of. This is a very good example of times you will have to rely on your pet exclusively for tanking. Crag spiders have a very strong poison that will drop you to half HP in about 1 minute. Not to mention that those things attack for about 40 - 50. As you probably guess, tanking here is simply NOT an option. And your trusty fire pet will die because of the poison here. which is why you need to start getting used to the water pet. :) The water pet is BY FAR the best "all - around" solo pet. Immune to poison, regen rate that would me a troll jealous, and relatively high AC/DEX/AGI across the board, and to boot, a decent DD. Right now I am hunting in the Lake of Ill Omen and the Sabertooth Grimalkins claw for about 50 - 70 and the Sarnak Conscripts Double attack for 40+. The only thing that doesnt go up with mages is our HP :) Very soon, this wont be an option. Also, try to understand WHY necs are always low on health... its because of the dark pact... they sacrifice their HP for mana.. meaning they have one advantage we will never have (without a manastone) and that is they will always be at full Mana. :) If you do what you are describing at higher levels, you will tank until you are at 1/4, then realize you cant cut it, and sit back and nuke. Mage spells are horribly mana inefficient. So basically at the end of the battle you are low on health AND low on mana. :) AND AND AND remember.... just cuz you win a fight, doesnt you will live long enough to walk away from it. When you aren't at full health and closer to death, many greens that would normally leave you alone will aggro on you. Just my 2 cp. <br><br>Nahualli Uoxtitla <br>Magician of the 28th Summon<br>Obsidian Legion <br>Tarew Marr</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
